            </item>
            <item xml:id="tribes">
               <!-- Tribes; in Erfassungstabelle S -->
               <label>12 Tribes</label>
               <p>
                  Represents the placements of the tents around the Tabernacle during their journey through the
                  desert. The tents are grouped towards the four cardinal directions as described in the First Book
                  of Numbers. Immediately next to Tabernacle are the four tents of the Levites; the twelves outer
                  medallions represent the other twelve tribes of <placeName>Israel</placeName>: <persName>Ruben</persName>, <persName>Simeon</persName>, <persName>Gad</persName> (south), <persName>Ephraim</persName>,
                  <persName>Benjamin</persName>, <persName>Menasseh</persName> (north), <persName>Maphtali</persName>, <persName>Asher</persName>, <persName>Dan</persName> (north), <persName>Zebulon</persName>, <persName>Issachar</persName>, and <persName>Judah</persName> (east).
                  The inscriptions on four inner medallions indicate number of cities each Levitic dynasty received
                  from the other tribes after the Israelites had conquered the promised land and it was distributed
                  among them. The interconnecting lines show which tribes gave these cities; for example the
                  Caaites at the top received ten cities from the tribes of <persName>Dan</persName>, <persName>Manasseh</persName> and <persName>Efraim</persName>.
               </p>
            </item>
