            <item xml:id="jerusalem">
               <label>Plan(s) of Jerusalem</label>
               <p>
                  Is formed of 3 concentric circles to denote three rings of walls. There are 6 arches denoting the
                  six gates. 3 interior spaces are inscribed:
                 <list type="living-quarters">
                     <item>habitatio regis et sacerdotum [living quarter of the king and priests]</item>
                     <item>habitatio nobilium civitati et prophetarum [living quarter nobles of the city and prophets]</item>
                     <item>habitatio vulgi [living quarter of the common people</item>
                  </list>
               6 gates are inscribed (clockwise from the top)
                  <list type="gates">
                     <item>porta sterquilinii (dung gate)</item>
                     <item>porta vetus vel iudiciaria (old gate or judgment gate)</item>
                     <item>porta piscium vel david (fish gate or David’s gate)</item>
                     <item>porta fontis syloe vel aquarum (gate of Pool of Siloah or water gate)</item>
                     <item>porta gregis vel probatice pisce vel offel vel negatiatorum (sheep gate or gate close to the ponds of gate of ophel or of the merchants)</item>
                     <item>porta vallis iosaphat vel geon (gate to the valley of Josaphat or Geon)</item>
                  </list>
               </p>
            </item>
